article.description: Marcus Evans made five 3-pointers and scored 26 points, Marcus Jackson added 20 points, and No. 5 seed Rice beat 12th-seeded Southern Mississippi 86-75 on Wednesday in the first round of the Conf
article.headline: Evans sparks Rice's win over Southern Miss in C-USA tourney
article.linkText: Evans sparks Rice's win over Southern Miss in C-USA tourney
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. -- Marcus Evans made five 3-pointers and scored 26 points, Marcus Jackson added 20 points, and No. 5 seed Rice beat 12th-seeded Southern Mississippi 86-75 on Wednesday in the first round of the Conference USA Tournament. Rice (22-10), which has won nine of 11, will face No. 4 seed UTEP on Thursday in the quarterfinals. Southern Miss jumped out to a 12-2 lead with seven points from Quinton Campbell. But Rice rallied to take a 35-33 lead on Evans' wide-open 3-pointer from the top of the key with 1:10 to go in the first half. Rice shot 50 percent in the half, including 7 of 15 from distance, but was hurt by 11 turnovers. Rice was ahead 68-67 and Evans scored the next nine points for a 10-point lead with 3:20 to go. Egor Koulechov made eight straight free throws and had 17 points and 12 rebounds for Rice, which was 29 of 32 from the line. Campbell led Southern Miss (9-22) with 23 points and eight rebounds. Cortez Edwards added 21 points with eight assists and Michael Ramey scored 10. The Golden Eagles have lost six straight in the series -- including three times this season.
